e name of the coin of Persian origin, used throughout the Caucasus (on behalf of Shah Abbas I, 1587-1629): <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>ʽabbāsī</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/> <w>abasi</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>abazi</w></mentioned>; the Ossetic form indicates Georgian as the closest source; here; also here <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/> <w>eppæz</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>apäsə</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(южные говоры) </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(South dialects) </note><w>абаз</w></mentioned>; cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_swari"/>; cf. also <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kapek6k9"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>66</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>